race.comment: BURN BOBBY BURN (3) resumes and has switched from a top Melbourne yard. He wasn't beaten too far at Geelong over 1512m first up last preparation and didn't have much luck. Just missed there following improving again. Nestor rides, and this is very winnable if he's primed up. KIRKALL (1) went close at Taree and will be fitter again. The longer sprint will suit and he should be in the finish. PINERO (12) resumed here and was beaten 1.5L with a 4kg claimer aboard. It was a good effort from a wide gate, and she has an inside barrier today with a senior hoop riding. She is still well shy of her Victorian best but is heading in the right direction. ALWAYS A RAINBOW (4) jumped a $2F here on debut over this distance and stalked the lead when missing by 1.6L. Will have taken plenty from that and Looker will push forward. Has plenty of scope for improvement. OAKFIELD MONTANA (7) debuts with Bullock engaged. Is likely better than the trial finishes suggest. A betting watch.
